# Mosbot API Rules Overview

Use these rules to keep the API consistent with existing patterns in `src/`.

## When to use each rule

- `server-bootstrap.mdc`: apply when editing `src/index.js` (middleware, routes, error handling).
- `express-routing.mdc`: apply for route modules under `src/routes/`.
- `api-responses.mdc`: apply when returning JSON or status codes from routes.
- `validation.mdc`: apply when validating request input in routes.
- `db-access.mdc`: apply when writing SQL queries or using the `pg` pool.
- `auth-jwt.mdc`: apply when changing login/register/verify or JWT protection.
- `openclaw-integration.mdc`: apply when working with OpenClaw workspace endpoints in `src/routes/openclaw.js`.

## General guidance

- Prefer existing patterns in neighboring files before introducing new ones.
- Keep response shapes and error formats consistent across endpoints.
- Use parameterized SQL and avoid string interpolation for user input.
